            . I am a <rs id="t17650417-61-viclabel342" type="occupation">waterman and lighter-man</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17650417-61-victim562 t17650417-61-viclabel342"></join>: I was at Gravesend when the things were lost, on the 21st of March: I only know the things to be my property; they are now at the Queen's-head here.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17650417-61-person564">
                  John 
                  Boulter 
               <interp inst="t17650417-61-person564" type="surname" value="Boulter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650417-61-person564" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650417-61-person564" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a waterman and lighter-man: on the 21st of March, between one and two in the morning, I took up the prisoner and another<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176504170042"></xptr> man in a boat, between Billinsgate and the Custom-house, on the water; they had this grapling-iron and rope in their boat, they were rowing off with them: we took them on shore and before my Lord Mayor: the other man made his escape out of the Mansion-house.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>The boat was adrift, and I went to bring her in; the rope was in her; there were two other lads with me; the other rowed our boat on shore: one was named 
               <persName id="t17650417-61-person565">
                  John 
                  Hinkins 
               <interp inst="t17650417-61-person565" type="surname" value="Hinkins"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650417-61-person565" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650417-61-person565" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and the other 
               <persName id="t17650417-61-person566">
                  John 
                  Pearcy 
               <interp inst="t17650417-61-person566" type="surname" value="Pearcy"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650417-61-person566" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650417-61-person566" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            : I sent to them; but they don't come near me.</p>
               <p>To his Character.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17650417-61-person567">
